PART 2 — Commercial Use (Revenue Sharing)
=============================================================================

If you wish to use this software, in whole or in part, in any product,
service, or project that generates revenue (including but not limited to
SaaS platforms, paid tools, consulting services, or ad-supported products),
the following terms apply:

1. REVENUE SHARE: You must pay the original author 5% (five percent) of
   gross revenue directly attributable to the use of this software or any
   derivative work based on it.

2. ATTRIBUTION: You must visibly credit the original author (Ana Luiza) in
   your product's interface or documentation, with a link to the original
   repository.

3. REPORTING: Revenue reports must be provided quarterly, within 30 days of
   the end of each calendar quarter.

4. AGREEMENT: Before generating any commercial revenue, you must contact the
   author to formalize the revenue sharing agreement in writing.

5. CONTACT: For commercial licensing inquiries, open an issue in this
   repository or contact the author directly.

